The paper deals with the problem of sparse recovery, which is a common topic in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of sub-linear time decoding suggests a focus on algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), while the need for numerical optimization techniques implies a connection to numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the extension of results for information-theoretically bounded adversaries suggests a possible connection to security and cryptography (cs.SI).
